Governor Aminu Bello Masari will tomorrow launch his re-election campaign in Funtua Local Government Area of Katsina State. The Chairman of Masari Campaign Council and Secretary to the State Government, Dr, Mustapha Inuwa, who addressed a press conference yesterday,  said the campaign team would go round all the 34 local government areas of the state. He said as loyal APC members, they would observe all laid down rules and regulation governing campaigns, adding that the achievement recorded by the Governor Masari-led administration in all sectors were there in all the nooks and crannies of the state to guarantee his reelection. According to him, completed projects would be commissioned in all the places visited. “Political defectors from other parties would also be officially received at their respective councils.” Why we can’t conduct LG polls — Masari Masari-Shema feud intensifies I have evidence to prosecute Shema – Gov. Masari